WEBVTT

01:09.486 --> 01:12.197
God damn it!

01:13.948 --> 01:15.158
I closed the gate.

01:15.867 --> 01:17.077
I can break through.

01:18.119 --> 01:19.037
What are you doing?

01:20.288 --> 01:21.539
I need food for my battery.

01:21.623 --> 01:24.709
You had a fully charged battery.
You didn't make a dent.

01:24.793 --> 01:28.213
No. We're not getting through that thing,
whatever it is, not this way at least.

01:28.296 --> 01:29.130
We have to.

01:29.214 --> 01:31.883
We don't even know
if Holly's on the other side.

01:31.966 --> 01:35.303
The trail could've gone cold
for a million reasons.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.765
Battery.

01:49.734 --> 01:50.777
Anything else?

01:50.860 --> 01:53.113
Hey! I… No, I don't have anything else.

01:53.196 --> 01:57.033
I was packing for a party of one,
a party of me.

01:58.076 --> 02:01.746
You're lucky I'm sharing with you.

02:06.334 --> 02:07.252
Try it.

02:08.670 --> 02:09.921
You might like it.

02:14.425 --> 02:15.343
Hmm?

02:26.813 --> 02:28.022
We gotta go.

02:39.492 --> 02:40.326
El?

02:40.869 --> 02:41.703
You okay?

02:41.786 --> 02:43.454
What's wrong? You all right?

02:52.255 --> 02:55.341
Will, Robin, I need you to answer me.

02:56.009 --> 02:58.970
I'm not mad.
I just need to know you're safe.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.518
Shit.

03:06.227 --> 03:07.312
-Is that, uh…
-Yeah.

03:07.395 --> 03:09.772
You think she saw us?

03:10.857 --> 03:12.108
Yeah.

03:20.116 --> 03:21.868
Get in.

03:24.787 --> 03:27.207
I told you, I explicitly told you,

03:27.290 --> 03:30.210
I didn't want him going anywhere
that's not safe.

03:30.293 --> 03:34.088
And not only did you take him,
you cut off all communication.

03:34.172 --> 03:37.467
Yes, I mean, in retrospect,
that was a bit inconsiderate.

03:37.550 --> 03:38.593
Inconsiderate?

03:38.676 --> 03:40.178
We really should've left a note.

03:40.261 --> 03:42.597
Is this funny to you?

03:42.680 --> 03:44.015
Oh. Sorry. It must be my tone.

03:44.098 --> 03:46.100
My mother says
I sound perpetually insincere.

03:46.184 --> 03:50.146
Okay, this is my son's life
you're playing with.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.564
My son.

03:51.648 --> 03:55.443
So next time I say
I do not want him leaving my side,

03:55.526 --> 03:59.072
that means I don't want him
leaving my goddamn side.

03:59.155 --> 04:00.448
I'm right here, Mom.

04:01.366 --> 04:03.368
You know, you can talk to me, right?

04:03.451 --> 04:04.994
And I'm not a kid anymore.

04:05.078 --> 04:07.121
Will, I am still your mother.

04:07.205 --> 04:09.332
-Doesn't mean you know what you're doing.
-What?

04:09.415 --> 04:11.459
Your plan? It… It sucked.

04:11.542 --> 04:12.710
I'm sorry, but it did.

04:12.794 --> 04:14.629
You only liked it because it was safe,

04:14.712 --> 04:16.798
but we don't have time for safe,
not anymore.

04:16.881 --> 04:19.884
We have to act, and we have to take risks,
and thank God we did.

04:19.968 --> 04:22.136
Because my plan, it… it actually worked.

04:22.220 --> 04:24.722
I spied on Vecna
and tapped back into the hive mind,

04:24.806 --> 04:27.141
and we found out
that Holly was just the beginning.

04:27.225 --> 04:28.768
Vecna is gonna take more kids.

04:28.851 --> 04:30.812
I don't know why
or what he wants to do with them,

04:30.895 --> 04:34.274
but now we know something
we can use against him, his next target.

04:35.066 --> 04:38.194
So next time you order me to stay
by your side, I wouldn't count on it.

04:39.654 --> 04:43.992
But, as I said, in the future,
we will try to leave a note.

04:45.618 --> 04:49.205
We should go. We have to stop Vecna.
We don't have much time.

05:09.851 --> 05:11.936
-Ready for the biosphere?
-Yes, I am.

05:12.020 --> 05:15.648
Okay. Think about the difference
between land and water.

05:15.732 --> 05:17.442
Okay, got it. Thank you!

05:18.693 --> 05:19.694
Hey!

07:01.546 --> 07:03.297
You still thinking about your parents?

07:04.841 --> 07:05.716
Yeah.

07:06.551 --> 07:09.470
They are in the very best possible hands,
Holly, I assure you.

07:10.054 --> 07:13.182
And I'm told that they are improving
with each hour that passes.

07:13.266 --> 07:15.101
As soon as they're healed,
they'll join us here.

07:15.768 --> 07:16.811
I… I know.

07:17.645 --> 07:19.564
-It's just--
-You wish to be with them.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.524
I understand.

07:22.024 --> 07:24.902
But you cannot offer them comfort
in Hawkins, Holly.

07:25.486 --> 07:28.156
The only comfort they have
is knowing you are here, safe.

07:28.990 --> 07:29.991
With me.

07:30.533 --> 07:31.909
Safe from the monsters.

07:35.455 --> 07:38.082
I thought blackberries
might cheer you up a little.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.293
They're your favorite, aren't they?

07:40.960 --> 07:41.961
How did you know?

07:42.670 --> 07:44.046
That they're my favorite?

07:44.130 --> 07:45.673
Oh, it's, uh…

07:45.756 --> 07:46.716
It's just a hunch.

07:47.300 --> 07:48.634
I'm good with hunches.

07:49.260 --> 07:52.638
Perhaps tomorrow
I'll make chocolate chip pancakes.

07:53.181 --> 07:55.391
-He loves those.
-Who does?

07:55.475 --> 07:56.851
Your classmate, Derek.

07:56.934 --> 07:58.686
Derek is coming here?

07:58.769 --> 08:01.647
You don't like Derek very much, do you?

08:04.192 --> 08:06.569
Should I just let the monsters eat him?

08:08.988 --> 08:11.574
No. No, you can't… you can't do that.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.077
Well, how about this?

08:15.161 --> 08:16.454
I will tell Derek

08:16.537 --> 08:20.166
that if he misbehaves,
or if he hurts you in any way,

08:20.249 --> 08:24.378
I will send him right back,
and he can face those monsters on his own.

08:24.462 --> 08:25.379
How does that sound?

08:32.303 --> 08:34.639
I expect to be gone most of the day.

08:34.722 --> 08:37.808
While I'm out, you'll have
the whole house all to yourself.

08:37.892 --> 08:39.227
The whole house?

08:39.310 --> 08:41.312
Everything which is mine is yours.

08:42.146 --> 08:44.982
But in return,
I need you to promise me one thing.

08:45.691 --> 08:48.277
Something very important.
Do you think you can do that?

08:48.361 --> 08:49.362
Yeah.

08:50.655 --> 08:55.701
You must never, under any circumstance,
go out into the woods. Do you understand?

08:57.286 --> 08:59.830
Is that where the monsters live?

09:01.207 --> 09:03.918
But they won't find you.
That is, as long as you don't--

09:04.001 --> 09:05.086
Don't try to find them.

09:07.088 --> 09:08.881
You know, I'm very glad I saved you first.

09:10.132 --> 09:11.884
You're the brightest of them all.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.807
Oh, and if you don't mind,
bring my mail in, won't you?

09:29.443 --> 09:30.444
How did you know?

09:31.153 --> 09:32.154
A hunch.

10:26.042 --> 10:27.460
Base, Alpha 1 checking in.

10:27.543 --> 10:30.046
We're arrived at checkpoint H,
H for Hercules.

10:30.129 --> 10:31.422
No sign of freak.

10:31.505 --> 10:34.842
We'll recon this area,
then proceed to next checkpoint. Over.

10:34.925 --> 10:38.387
Alpha 1, Base. Acknowledge
your location at Hercules. Over.

10:38.471 --> 10:39.639
Alpha 1, out.

10:40.514 --> 10:41.474
Recon?

10:42.475 --> 10:43.851
Meaning, I take a leak,

10:44.352 --> 10:46.062
and you guys take five.

10:47.730 --> 10:50.399
You heard the man.
Smoke 'em if you got 'em.

11:40.658 --> 11:42.910
Some jackass messing with the wall,
Lieutenant?

11:43.703 --> 11:45.037
Some jackass, yeah.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.374
But not one of ours.

11:50.209 --> 11:51.210
Come on.

11:55.172 --> 11:56.507
Get on the hedgehog.

11:57.675 --> 11:58.592
Yes, sir.

12:44.597 --> 12:45.931
-Oh!
-Hey!

12:51.020 --> 12:51.854
Come up! Come up!

12:51.937 --> 12:54.899
Base, Alpha 1, we're taking enemy fire.
Need backup and air cover now.

12:55.900 --> 12:57.651
Move!

13:26.889 --> 13:28.098
Okay.

13:32.520 --> 13:34.063
Who's there?

15:11.118 --> 15:13.162
It looks like
Robin sent up the Bat-Signal.

15:29.511 --> 15:31.472
Hey. I'm so sorry.

15:32.389 --> 15:33.307
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

15:33.390 --> 15:34.266
Here.

15:36.018 --> 15:37.853
Holy shit.

15:37.937 --> 15:38.979
Yep.

15:39.063 --> 15:41.857
Bike crash.
Flew headfirst into a light post.

15:42.566 --> 15:45.778
Look, I'm sorry about missing the crawl,
about everything.

15:45.861 --> 15:47.988
It's not your fault.
Don't beat yourself up.

15:48.072 --> 15:49.782
Yeah, looks like he already did.

15:49.865 --> 15:51.241
-Is that broken?
-I dunno.

15:51.325 --> 15:52.660
-Let me…
-Don't touch it. Why--

15:52.743 --> 15:54.703
-I wasn't…. I wanted to…
-You were going to.

15:54.787 --> 15:57.706
Hey, this isn't a social call, kiddos.
Let's go.

16:03.087 --> 16:04.254
Derek?

16:04.338 --> 16:05.381
Derek Turnbow?

16:05.464 --> 16:09.051
As in the Turnbow family?
Like Turnbow Realty?

16:09.134 --> 16:10.552
The one and only.

16:10.636 --> 16:12.554
Whole family's a menace.

16:12.638 --> 16:14.014
How can you be sure?

16:14.098 --> 16:16.225
Sure that Derek's the next target?

16:16.308 --> 16:18.394
Because I saw.

16:19.144 --> 16:22.022
I've learned that
when I'm close enough to the hive mind,

16:22.106 --> 16:24.400
I can tap into it, into Vecna's mind.

16:24.483 --> 16:26.443
I can see who he's targeting.

16:27.194 --> 16:30.030
The first time it happened,
I saw through Holly's eyes

16:30.114 --> 16:31.865
the same day she was taken.

16:33.492 --> 16:35.661
And this morning, it happened again.

16:38.247 --> 16:40.332
Only this time, I wasn't Holly.

16:40.416 --> 16:42.001
-What the hell?
-I was someone else.

16:42.084 --> 16:44.336
-Watch where you're going, dipshit.
-Suck a fat one!

16:44.920 --> 16:46.880
I was Derek Turnbow. I'm positive.

16:46.964 --> 16:48.007
Hold on. I'm a little lost.

16:48.090 --> 16:49.216
Shocking.

16:49.299 --> 16:53.012
Were you seeing through the eyes
of… of Vecna or of Derek?

16:53.095 --> 16:54.263
Both.

16:54.346 --> 16:55.973
I… I was Vecna,

16:56.056 --> 16:58.559
but inside Derek's mind.

16:58.642 --> 17:00.936
Vecna's like a psychic serial killer.

17:01.020 --> 17:04.314
He stalks his victims,
but he does it by invading their minds.

17:04.398 --> 17:06.650
That's what he did with Chrissy and Max.

17:06.734 --> 17:09.361
Yeah, but the way
he's doing it this time is different.

17:09.987 --> 17:13.407
We did some digging at the hospital.
It turns out that before he took Holly,

17:13.490 --> 17:14.575
Vecna stalked her.

17:14.658 --> 17:18.454
But… he didn't appear as Vecna.
He appeared as Henry.

17:19.204 --> 17:20.039
As a friend.

17:20.122 --> 17:22.124
We think he was trying to earn her trust.

17:22.207 --> 17:24.251
Now, why he went to all that trouble,
we don't know.

17:24.334 --> 17:26.879
But I highly doubt
his long-term goal is friendship.

17:26.962 --> 17:29.548
Whatever it is, whatever he's planning,

17:30.174 --> 17:31.467
we have to stop him.

17:32.009 --> 17:33.719
And we have to save Derek.

17:34.762 --> 17:36.096
The Turnbows live here.

17:36.180 --> 17:37.806
We wait in a van across the street.

17:37.890 --> 17:40.642
As soon as they're asleep,
we move in, we grab Derek,

17:40.726 --> 17:43.270
and we take him to here,

17:43.353 --> 17:46.440
the McCorkle farm.
It's completely isolated. It's abandoned.

17:46.523 --> 17:51.361
The only thing is, we need to make sure
he doesn't see us or know where he is.

17:51.445 --> 17:52.738
So we'll need to blindfold him.

17:52.821 --> 17:54.490
Wait. Hold on. What?

17:54.573 --> 17:55.949
So that Vecna can't find him.

17:56.033 --> 17:59.745
Yeah. What, and Mom,
you're okay with just kidnapping a child?

17:59.828 --> 18:02.664
No, we're saving a child via kidnapping.

18:02.748 --> 18:04.249
And yeah, it's fine,

18:04.333 --> 18:05.167
I think.

18:05.250 --> 18:08.337
Yes. Now's not the time
to play it safe, Jonathan.

18:08.420 --> 18:10.172
If I may,

18:10.255 --> 18:13.550
though I'm not morally opposed
to any of this, there are a few holes.

18:13.634 --> 18:17.679
Yeah. Like what if Derek falls asleep
before the Demogorgon attacks him?

18:17.763 --> 18:18.680
That's one.

18:18.764 --> 18:22.935
Or what if Derek wakes up
before we grab him, alerts his family?

18:23.018 --> 18:25.020
-We'll go to jail.
-There's another.

18:25.104 --> 18:27.981
But the third and most gaping hole is

18:28.065 --> 18:30.651
even if by some miracle
this plan even works,

18:31.151 --> 18:32.277
Holly's still missing.

18:33.070 --> 18:34.947
Hop and El, still MIA.

18:35.030 --> 18:37.199
This doesn't bring us any closer
to finding Vecna.

18:37.282 --> 18:39.827
This plan just buys us
and Derek some time.

18:39.910 --> 18:40.786
That's it.

18:40.869 --> 18:42.329
Not necessarily.

18:42.412 --> 18:43.622
There might be a way.

18:44.915 --> 18:47.668
A way to save Derek and find Holly.

18:51.713 --> 18:52.548
This is Derek.

18:54.007 --> 18:56.885
And this is the rest
of the Turnbow family.

18:58.053 --> 19:00.681
We're gonna need to recruit someone
that the family trusts,

19:00.764 --> 19:02.558
someone that can gain access to the house.

19:04.017 --> 19:05.894
This person will knock the family out.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.521
Then we'll extract the family.

19:07.604 --> 19:08.605
Knock them out?

19:08.689 --> 19:11.441
Well, safely.
With sleeping pills or something.

19:11.525 --> 19:13.443
I might know
where we could get some benzos.

19:13.527 --> 19:15.737
Those things could knock an elephant
on its ass.

19:15.821 --> 19:17.489
Perfect. That way if Vecna spies,

19:17.573 --> 19:19.783
he'll just assume
Derek is fast asleep in bed.

19:19.867 --> 19:21.493
He'll send his Demos to grab him.

19:22.369 --> 19:24.997
Only he won't find Derek. He'll find us.

19:25.581 --> 19:26.540
And we'll be ready.

19:26.623 --> 19:29.334
We'll get Murray to supply us
with the traps.

19:29.418 --> 19:32.212
We'll burn the sucker.
Send him scampering home to its master,

19:32.296 --> 19:34.506
but not before we stick him
with one of these.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.427
We'll track the Demo
across the Upside Down

19:38.510 --> 19:40.846
in the Squawk van
just like we did with Hopper.

19:40.929 --> 19:44.308
And if we're lucky,
the Demo will lead us back to its lair,

19:44.391 --> 19:45.392
to Vecna,

19:46.185 --> 19:47.186
to Holly.

19:48.770 --> 19:49.605
Holes?

19:57.487 --> 20:00.073
Children behave

20:01.074 --> 20:04.244
That's what they say
When we're together

20:04.745 --> 20:08.332
'Cause what would they say

20:08.415 --> 20:10.250
If they ever knew and so we're

20:11.627 --> 20:14.004
Running just as fast as we can

20:15.088 --> 20:17.925
Holdin' onto one another's hand

20:18.425 --> 20:21.428
Tryin' to get away into the night

20:21.511 --> 20:23.722
And then you put your arms around me

20:23.805 --> 20:26.683
And we tumble to the ground
And then you say

20:26.767 --> 20:29.603
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

20:29.686 --> 20:33.523
There doesn't seem to be anyone around

20:34.149 --> 20:36.818
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

20:36.902 --> 20:40.989
The beating of our hearts
Is the only sound

20:41.073 --> 20:44.701
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

20:48.956 --> 20:51.750
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

20:51.833 --> 20:55.003
The beating of our hearts
Is the only sound

20:56.338 --> 20:59.091
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

20:59.174 --> 21:02.177
There doesn't seem to be anyone around

21:03.428 --> 21:06.556
-I think we're alone now
-Alone now

21:22.698 --> 21:23.657
Henry?

21:25.867 --> 21:29.413
Derek, if this is you,
it's not funny, you barf bag!

22:08.243 --> 22:09.578
"I need your help."

22:09.661 --> 22:11.330
"Meet me at the X."

22:12.247 --> 22:13.290
"Henry."

22:23.884 --> 22:24.718
East.

22:44.237 --> 22:47.074
Move aside.
Coming through! Make way, please!

22:47.157 --> 22:49.201
You're gonna be okay, man.
Just hang in there.

22:53.330 --> 22:54.289
Sir!

22:55.499 --> 22:56.375
Orders?

22:59.044 --> 23:00.212
Find who did this.

23:01.171 --> 23:02.130
Bring them to me.

23:02.631 --> 23:05.467
And I will disembowel the son of a bitch!

23:05.550 --> 23:06.676
Sir!

23:06.760 --> 23:08.303
Let's go! Move out!

23:17.687 --> 23:20.232
Got that Humvee hid pretty good.

23:20.315 --> 23:23.193
If they don't know it's missing yet,
they will soon.

23:23.276 --> 23:24.444
Got more birds.

23:24.528 --> 23:26.863
They all got those speakers,
whatever they are.

23:30.784 --> 23:32.577
I don't know how, but…

23:33.495 --> 23:36.415
seems like our military friends
found your kryptonite.

23:39.251 --> 23:40.252
Hey.

23:41.211 --> 23:42.754
Any movement from our guest?

23:46.383 --> 23:47.884
Better not be brain-dead.

23:53.557 --> 23:54.808
He peed on it.

23:57.727 --> 23:58.603
What?

24:00.272 --> 24:01.565
That soldier.

24:02.190 --> 24:03.817
You said he peed on the big wall.

24:03.900 --> 24:05.485
Yeah, no, I heard what you said.

24:05.569 --> 24:07.737
I just don't know
why you're talking about it.

24:08.572 --> 24:10.115
Maybe he knows what it is…

24:11.199 --> 24:12.367
or how to get through it.

24:13.160 --> 24:14.703
That's highly doubtful.

24:15.287 --> 24:16.830
What he will know, though,

24:17.581 --> 24:19.708
is the schedule
for the next supply convoy,

24:19.791 --> 24:22.419
which is our way out of this hellhole.

24:24.212 --> 24:25.338
What happens then?

24:27.591 --> 24:31.261
We go back,
we tell everybody what we saw, and we… we…

24:32.012 --> 24:33.346
make a new plan.

24:34.347 --> 24:38.143
The others? You think
they'll know how to get through the wall?

24:40.145 --> 24:41.646
I don't know. Maybe, yeah.

24:41.730 --> 24:42.814
They won't.

24:43.565 --> 24:44.941
We'll be back to the first square.

24:45.025 --> 24:46.818
-Square one.
-He peed on it.

24:46.902 --> 24:48.862
Even if he knows something,

24:48.945 --> 24:51.281
he's been trained to resist interrogation.

24:51.990 --> 24:54.159
The Russians took two weeks
trying to break me,

24:54.242 --> 24:55.785
and they still couldn't.

24:55.869 --> 24:58.538
We don't have two weeks.
We don't have two hours.

24:59.164 --> 25:02.083
Convoy information,
I might be able to get out of him.

25:02.667 --> 25:05.378
Classified information?
That's not gonna happen.

25:06.087 --> 25:07.255
With my help, it will.

25:07.339 --> 25:08.340
Oh, yeah, I'm sorry.

25:08.423 --> 25:11.468
I forgot about your extensive training
in interrogation tactics.

25:11.551 --> 25:12.844
My battery's charged.

25:12.928 --> 25:14.513
I don't see how that helps us.

25:14.596 --> 25:16.056
-I can break him.
-El…

25:16.139 --> 25:17.182
Twenty minutes.

25:17.766 --> 25:20.268
You get to ask him about the convoy.

25:20.352 --> 25:21.853
You get what you want,

25:22.437 --> 25:23.772
then I get what I want.

25:25.190 --> 25:29.486
Compromise. "C-O-M-promise." Remember?

25:29.569 --> 25:30.737
Halfway happy.

25:30.820 --> 25:33.240
Hey, what is this?

25:33.865 --> 25:36.618
Get me outta here!
Get me the hell outta here!

25:36.701 --> 25:38.787
You're a stubborn punk-ass.
You know that, right?

25:41.790 --> 25:43.792
Einstein-Rosen bridges,

25:43.875 --> 25:46.169
more commonly known as wormholes,

25:46.253 --> 25:48.964
are often depicted
in an hourglass-like shape,

25:49.047 --> 25:50.048
such as this.

25:50.840 --> 25:54.010
While the existence of wormholes
is entirely theoretical,

25:54.094 --> 25:55.637
they have captured the fascination

25:55.720 --> 25:59.015
of scientists
and science fiction writers alike.

25:59.099 --> 26:00.976
Can anyone tell me why that is?

26:03.562 --> 26:05.772
Come on. This is easy. Just…

26:06.648 --> 26:08.692
What's neat about wormholes?

26:11.570 --> 26:13.071
Okay. Erica.

26:13.822 --> 26:14.739
Wormholes are neat

26:14.823 --> 26:18.493
because they allow matter to travel
between galaxies or dimensions

26:18.577 --> 26:20.370
without crossing the space between.

26:20.453 --> 26:22.372
Yes. Exactly right.

26:22.872 --> 26:24.040
Again.

26:24.124 --> 26:28.878
And, uh, just think of all the places
mankind could go.

26:28.962 --> 26:30.630
Another galaxy.

26:30.714 --> 26:32.424
Another time, even.

26:32.507 --> 26:34.676
So why aren't we doing it now?

26:34.759 --> 26:39.556
If wormholes did exist,
they would be extraordinarily unstable.

26:39.639 --> 26:43.268
Their enormous gravitational force
would rip them apart

26:43.351 --> 26:46.313
at the very moment they formed. Now…

26:51.484 --> 26:55.405
You have 60 seconds to explain
why you interrupted my favorite class.

26:55.488 --> 26:57.907
Erica, this is really serious.

26:57.991 --> 26:59.993
57, 56…

27:00.076 --> 27:02.454
It's hard
to explain everything in 56 seconds.

27:02.537 --> 27:05.957
But basically, everything went bad
at the crawl last night.

27:06.041 --> 27:07.500
Wouldn't know. I wasn't invited.

27:07.584 --> 27:09.461
That's why I'm ex--

27:10.253 --> 27:12.005
That's why I'm explaining.

27:12.088 --> 27:15.133
Things went bad at the crawl,
and a lot of stuff happened,

27:15.216 --> 27:17.719
and now we think
Tina's little brother's in trouble.

27:17.802 --> 27:19.429
That literally makes no sense.

27:19.512 --> 27:22.932
And even if it did, why would I care
that Dipshit Derek is in trouble?

27:23.016 --> 27:25.060
You're just gonna have to trust us, okay?

27:25.143 --> 27:28.855
And to help Derek, we're gonna need you
to get us into the Turnbow house.

27:28.938 --> 27:30.106
-Tonight.
-Not possible.

27:30.190 --> 27:32.192
Of course it is.
Make plans to hang out with Tina.

27:32.275 --> 27:35.195
-Tina and I don't hang.
-You hang nonstop. She's your best friend.

27:35.278 --> 27:36.196
-Was.
-Was?

27:36.279 --> 27:37.530
-We are now enemies.
-Enemies?

27:37.614 --> 27:38.823
-Arch.
-Since when?

27:38.907 --> 27:40.617
Since PE class 12 days ago.

27:40.700 --> 27:43.036
Then apologize for what happened
in PE class 12 days ago.

27:43.119 --> 27:45.038
-No can do.
-Yes, can do.

27:45.121 --> 27:49.459
All you have to do is use your mouth
to form a word that rhymes with "starry."

27:49.542 --> 27:52.587
I'd rather learn about wormholes
than apologize to Tina

27:52.671 --> 27:55.006
and help you all save Dipshit Derek.

27:55.090 --> 27:57.050
Sorry.

27:58.301 --> 27:59.302
Time's up.

28:00.720 --> 28:03.890
This isn't about saving Derek.
It's about saving Holly.

28:05.308 --> 28:06.393
Vecna took her.

28:07.018 --> 28:10.730
And yeah, now he's after Dipshit Derek.
But we have a plan.

28:10.814 --> 28:13.983
A plan to both save Dipshit Derek
and find Holly.

28:14.067 --> 28:15.694
But the plan is…

28:15.777 --> 28:17.278
It's a bit insane.

28:17.362 --> 28:18.571
But after it's over,

28:19.114 --> 28:21.950
I don't think
Tina's gonna wanna talk to you ever again.

28:22.909 --> 28:25.245
Well, why the hell
didn't you just start with that?

28:35.255 --> 28:36.214
Hi, Doris.

28:36.297 --> 28:38.633
Oh! You here to see Mrs. Massey?

28:38.717 --> 28:41.886
-You are just psychic, I'm telling you.
-I am. Thank you, baby.

28:41.970 --> 28:44.055
-Thank you.
-Y'all go on back there.

28:45.724 --> 28:46.891
Mm!

28:46.975 --> 28:48.101
Who's Mrs. Massey?

28:48.184 --> 28:50.311
My sweet granny
who fell down a flight of stairs

28:50.395 --> 28:52.522
and broke nearly every bone
in her frail old body.

28:52.605 --> 28:54.107
Oh God. I'm sorry.

28:54.190 --> 28:56.234
Don't be too sorry.
She's not my real granny.

28:56.317 --> 28:58.027
I use her name so I can visit Vickie.

28:58.111 --> 29:00.655
I know it sounds unethical,
but I always bring her cookies,

29:00.739 --> 29:03.616
and I think Mrs. Massey loves me
more than her own family at this point.

29:03.700 --> 29:07.162
More importantly, she has got, like,
a mondo stash of benzos,

29:07.245 --> 29:09.873
and her nurse is a slacker
who never locks the medicine cabinet.

29:09.956 --> 29:11.207
…this story I heard.

29:11.291 --> 29:12.459
-Shit.
-Oh!

29:13.251 --> 29:15.295
-What… What are we doing?
-Hiding.

29:15.378 --> 29:17.380
-Hiding? Right. Why?
-Down.

29:22.927 --> 29:24.888
Jesus, she talks so much.

29:24.971 --> 29:26.473
-I know. I'm a hypocrite.
-I…

29:26.556 --> 29:27.640
We have to go!

29:32.479 --> 29:36.149
I promised Vickie
that I would take her to Enzo's tonight,

29:36.232 --> 29:38.151
and now I can't, obviously,

29:38.234 --> 29:39.778
meaning I have to ditch her again

29:39.861 --> 29:42.739
for reasons
that she just can't understand.

29:42.822 --> 29:46.201
A massive fight will ensue, and we'll
never make it to my fake granny's room.

29:46.284 --> 29:48.286
I can't be the reason
Wheeler's plan fails.

29:48.369 --> 29:50.538
-Okay?
-Okay.

29:53.374 --> 29:54.375
Shoot. Stay low.

30:02.884 --> 30:06.805
You know,
you could always just kiss her again.

30:07.388 --> 30:09.599
I knew that was your goddamn bowl cut.

30:09.682 --> 30:13.311
Yeah, I mean,
they're not that popular anymore.

30:14.229 --> 30:16.439
Did I look like
I knew what I was doing at least?

30:16.523 --> 30:19.400
I mean, yeah. To me.

30:20.735 --> 30:22.153
I guess that's something.

30:22.237 --> 30:25.323
So, how did you know
that, with Vickie, right?

30:25.949 --> 30:27.909
How did you know that Vickie wanted to…

30:27.992 --> 30:29.160
-Make out?
-…to date?

30:29.244 --> 30:32.872
Oh. Well, we volunteered together.
You know, there were, like, signals.

30:32.956 --> 30:34.123
Signals?

30:34.207 --> 30:38.044
Yeah, you know, like a brush of the knee,
a bump of the elbow, a shared look.

30:38.753 --> 30:42.173
It all just kind of accrued,
like a snowball rolling down a hill,

30:42.257 --> 30:43.299
until it was obvious.

30:44.217 --> 30:45.426
How obvious?

30:46.553 --> 30:50.473
Let's say the, uh, snowball
became an avalanche.

31:00.400 --> 31:02.735
Oh God, that looks awful.

31:02.819 --> 31:03.736
Sure does.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.364
And he's in the same wing
as my fake granny.

31:06.948 --> 31:08.867
-Meaning?
-Same slacker nurse.

31:11.494 --> 31:12.787
Jackpot.

31:12.871 --> 31:15.623
Jesus, we could knock out half of Hawkins
with this shit.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.876
-Okay, load me up.
-Okay.

31:27.176 --> 31:29.178
Okay, so, I couldn't get any ethanol,

31:29.262 --> 31:33.558
but I was able to scrounge up
a gallon of acetone.

31:33.641 --> 31:34.475
Be very careful.

31:34.559 --> 31:38.021
You smoke a Virginia Slim too close
to this stuff, it'll catch fire, okay?

31:38.897 --> 31:41.482
Snare wire, various gauges.

31:41.566 --> 31:45.486
A creepy, child-sized CPR dummy.

31:45.570 --> 31:47.572
Its purpose a mystery to me.

31:49.073 --> 31:52.577
Shotgun shells,
per our lovely lady's request.

31:53.870 --> 31:57.248
Three 20-packs of water balloons.
Purpose also a mystery.

31:57.332 --> 32:00.460
But I did take the liberty
of selecting the grenade style

32:00.543 --> 32:03.087
as it felt thematically appropriate.

32:03.963 --> 32:06.299
Do keep those far away from…

32:08.760 --> 32:10.595
these 3,000 feet of barbed wire.

32:10.678 --> 32:12.764
Oh, I almost forgot.

32:13.514 --> 32:16.517
Some sparkling new spark plugs
for Bilbo Baggins.

32:19.228 --> 32:20.521
Spark plugs, that's it?

32:20.605 --> 32:22.315
I'm also giving out free hugs.

32:22.398 --> 32:24.108
-You didn't get the turbocharger?
-No.

32:24.192 --> 32:25.526
-The suspension kit?
-No.

32:25.610 --> 32:27.111
-The aerodynamic spoiler?
-No.

32:27.195 --> 32:29.280
It wasn't a goddamn Christmas list,
Murray.

32:30.031 --> 32:31.574
That's exactly what it was.

32:31.658 --> 32:35.119
And the fact that Santa Murray scrounged
all this up in a single afternoon

32:35.203 --> 32:39.082
and smuggled it into what is likely
the most heavily secured location

32:39.165 --> 32:42.251
outside of the White House,
Fort Knox, and Area 51

32:42.335 --> 32:44.462
is a goddamn Christmas miracle.

32:44.545 --> 32:46.839
So, count your blessings,

32:46.923 --> 32:49.092
hang some mistletoe, pucker up,

32:49.175 --> 32:51.844
and kiss my jolly ass!

32:54.597 --> 32:56.599
Thank you for the spark plugs.

33:07.360 --> 33:09.529
-What are you doing?
-You gonna help or just stand there?

33:09.612 --> 33:11.906
I'd rather not herniate a disc
over a lost cause.

33:11.990 --> 33:13.825
Yeah, that's the attitude.

33:13.908 --> 33:16.327
This van once stalled out
chugging up Pickett Road

33:16.411 --> 33:18.121
like it was
the Little Engine That Couldn't.

33:18.204 --> 33:21.708
It's not fast enough to keep up
with a Demo without serious modifications.

33:21.791 --> 33:24.252
What the hell do you think I'm doing?
Modifying.

33:25.003 --> 33:27.255
A lighter van is a faster van.

33:27.755 --> 33:30.717
If we're just tracking,
we don't need half of the crap in here.

33:30.800 --> 33:33.469
Speaking of, can you go
empty the window washer fluid?

33:33.553 --> 33:36.431
The window washer fluid.
That'll do it. Good job, Steven.

33:36.514 --> 33:38.641
We should go back
to the agreement from yesterday.

33:38.725 --> 33:41.227
-What agreement?
-The no-talking agreement.

33:50.486 --> 33:52.488
Oh yeah

33:54.198 --> 33:56.117
What are you doing?
Henderson, I'm using that.

33:56.200 --> 33:57.952
Hey. You little shit!

33:58.036 --> 33:59.704
I said I'm using that, man.

33:59.787 --> 34:01.789
What are you-- Yo, hey!

34:01.873 --> 34:04.333
Get off the Beamer, man. Get off!

34:04.417 --> 34:06.169
You were right. For once.

34:06.252 --> 34:08.629
We don't need half the crap in there
for our mission.

34:08.713 --> 34:12.675
In fact, the only thing
we really need is a telemetry tracker,

34:12.759 --> 34:15.386
which I can affix to any vehicle.

34:15.470 --> 34:16.345
Henderson…

34:16.929 --> 34:17.972
Don't you touch her.

34:18.681 --> 34:19.724
Henderson!

34:19.807 --> 34:21.559
Henderson, I'm dead serious.

34:22.477 --> 34:24.937
-No talking.
-Wait, wait, wait!

34:25.021 --> 34:26.522
Hey, hey! What are you…

34:26.606 --> 34:28.399
No! What the…

34:31.694 --> 34:33.446
-Okay, transmitter?
-Yeah.

34:33.529 --> 34:35.948
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Children. Children.

34:36.824 --> 34:39.452
-What are we doing?
-What does it look like?

34:39.535 --> 34:45.625
Well, it looks like you're loading
my telemetry tracker into a shotgun shell

34:45.708 --> 34:47.585
in what I presume are the hopes

34:47.668 --> 34:50.505
of firing it
into an interdimensional being.

34:50.588 --> 34:52.590
You told me that these transmitters

34:52.673 --> 34:56.177
were designed specifically
to withstand harsh conditions.

34:56.260 --> 35:00.681
Blasting it out of a shotgun
into some beast isn't a harsh condition.

35:00.765 --> 35:01.641
It's deadly.

35:01.724 --> 35:05.353
If the heat from the exploding gunpowder
doesn't destroy the transmitter,

35:05.436 --> 35:07.063
the force from the recoil will.

35:07.146 --> 35:09.649
And is that a fact

35:09.732 --> 35:11.609
or… a theory?

35:14.362 --> 35:15.279
A theory.

35:15.363 --> 35:16.948
Oh. Okay.

35:18.491 --> 35:19.784
Let's test it then.

35:22.745 --> 35:24.247
What's her deal today, huh?

35:24.330 --> 35:25.581
Her deal?

35:25.665 --> 35:26.666
Yeah.

35:27.291 --> 35:30.962
Her sister is missing.
Her parents almost died.

35:31.045 --> 35:34.006
-Sure, sure. But what about, you know?
-No, I don't.

35:34.090 --> 35:35.591
Coltrane, Love Supreme.

35:35.675 --> 35:37.677
-Did you give it a whirl?
-Yeah.

35:37.760 --> 35:39.637
-And?
-It was very nice.

35:39.720 --> 35:41.764
-And?
-What? Thank you?

35:41.848 --> 35:43.975
Christ, man!
You haven't done it yet, have you?

35:44.559 --> 35:47.478
I thought you were desperate,
that things were stagnating,

35:47.562 --> 35:49.355
that your mating competition
was making moves.

35:49.438 --> 35:50.439
-Whoa!
-Hey!

35:50.523 --> 35:54.026
Whatever you two are conspiring about
back there, please do it later.

35:54.110 --> 35:55.653
Our apologies, milady.

35:55.736 --> 35:57.655
And hurry up. We don't have all day.

35:59.699 --> 36:00.950
Why the delay?

36:01.033 --> 36:02.076
Have you forgotten the fact

36:02.160 --> 36:04.996
that her sister is missing
and her parents are in the hospital?

36:05.079 --> 36:07.039
Could one ask for better conditions?

36:07.123 --> 36:10.543
The death of a loved one
is the painful but necessary reminder

36:10.626 --> 36:13.379
that life is delicate, precious,

36:13.462 --> 36:16.132
that one must not take those around us
for granted,

36:16.215 --> 36:17.925
that one must strengthen bonds.

36:18.009 --> 36:19.093
I mean, hell, man,

36:19.177 --> 36:22.763
the two of you were brought together
by shared trauma in the first place.

36:22.847 --> 36:25.057
This is the stuff of fate, of destiny.

36:25.141 --> 36:27.268
So, if not for your sake, then for mine.

36:27.351 --> 36:29.979
Grow some balls
and get it over with already.

36:30.062 --> 36:32.773
Hey! If you don't shut up
right now, Santa,

36:32.857 --> 36:36.444
I swear to God I will shoot this tracker
into your potato sacks.

36:37.028 --> 36:38.863
I'm a good enough shot to hit any mark,

36:39.530 --> 36:40.656
no matter how small.

36:40.740 --> 36:41.866
Jesus.

36:41.949 --> 36:43.367
Now set up my target.

36:43.993 --> 36:44.994
Okay.

36:56.589 --> 36:57.965
Quite large, actually.

36:58.549 --> 37:01.052
My… potato sacks.

37:04.764 --> 37:05.765
Hmm.

37:14.982 --> 37:17.944
Well, would you look at that, Santa?
Another miracle.

37:19.820 --> 37:21.113
At the very least,

37:21.781 --> 37:23.282
couldn't hurt her mood.

37:45.972 --> 37:46.973
Hey!

37:47.640 --> 37:48.641
How's the head?

37:49.308 --> 37:51.060
You'll get nothing out of me.

37:51.560 --> 37:53.854
So if you're gonna kill me, get to it.

37:53.938 --> 37:55.231
It's tempting.

37:56.148 --> 37:57.149
But no.

37:58.192 --> 38:00.403
Just need a little information, okay?

38:02.822 --> 38:05.157
I need to know about that fleshy wall.

38:07.118 --> 38:09.161
Don't know a thing about it.
I'm just a grunt.

38:09.745 --> 38:11.580
A grunt?

38:12.164 --> 38:13.291
Is that funny to you?

38:13.791 --> 38:16.168
Let me get this straight.
You're telling me you just,

38:16.252 --> 38:19.922
like all the other boots on the ground,
came to Hawkins to direct traffic

38:20.006 --> 38:21.590
and save kitty cats out of trees.

38:21.674 --> 38:24.635
-You're just a red, white, and blue grunt.
-That's what I said.

38:25.720 --> 38:27.263
I used to be a grunt.

38:29.098 --> 38:30.558
So I know the difference.

38:33.227 --> 38:34.645
You're something else.

38:35.396 --> 38:37.773
Some kind of special forces puke.

38:38.774 --> 38:41.485
I used to have to put up
with guys like you in Nam.

38:41.569 --> 38:44.155
Guys who cut the ears off enemy corpses,

38:44.238 --> 38:45.906
make a necklace out of them.

38:46.490 --> 38:48.200
Pretty sick, you ask me.

38:49.201 --> 38:53.080
Grunt, my ass.
You're one of Sullivan's attack dogs.

38:54.123 --> 38:56.208
You're the psychos
he lets slip off the leash

38:56.292 --> 38:58.878
when he wants to,
I don't know, go into the desert

38:58.961 --> 39:03.341
and massacre a group of unarmed scientists
all in the pursuit of one little girl.

39:03.424 --> 39:04.675
Little… Little girl?

39:05.509 --> 39:06.510
She's a freak!

39:07.219 --> 39:10.139
She took down a helicopter
just by looking at it.

39:10.222 --> 39:11.557
I had friends in that Huey, man.

39:11.640 --> 39:14.060
Oh my God! My heart is breaking for you.

39:14.143 --> 39:16.645
You, whoever you are,
you just took out more of my guys,

39:16.729 --> 39:18.105
so go to hell.

39:18.189 --> 39:20.191
I'm already there. Look around you.

39:20.274 --> 39:22.777
I gotta tell you something
about this old ex-grunt.

39:22.860 --> 39:26.030
Those guys I killed,
I'd kill them a hundred times over.

39:26.822 --> 39:29.075
I'd kill a thousand guys like you

39:29.158 --> 39:30.910
to protect the one person that I love.

39:35.247 --> 39:36.207
All right.

39:37.249 --> 39:39.460
So you don't know about the wall, huh?

39:40.252 --> 39:41.504
Who does?

39:42.505 --> 39:43.381
Dr. Kay?

39:45.341 --> 39:47.051
-Who?
-Kay.

39:47.551 --> 39:49.553
The one
that even Sullivan takes orders from.

39:50.596 --> 39:52.723
-Don't know who you're talking about.
-Really?

39:53.391 --> 39:54.850
Then why'd you tell us her name?

39:54.934 --> 39:55.893
What?

39:55.976 --> 39:59.522
Her name. You told us her name.

39:59.605 --> 40:00.523
Us?

40:01.023 --> 40:03.526
That little girl you're looking for?

40:03.609 --> 40:07.071
She's rooting around
in that tiny brain of yours as we speak.

40:07.154 --> 40:09.240
She can see everything.

40:09.323 --> 40:12.785
Everything you've ever thought,
everything you've ever seen.

40:12.868 --> 40:14.745
So you might as well start talking.

40:14.829 --> 40:17.456
'Cause if you don't give me answers,
she'll find them.

40:17.540 --> 40:19.667
So why don't we save some time?

40:20.376 --> 40:22.128
Where do I find Dr. Kay?

40:22.211 --> 40:24.839
I… I don't know where she is.

40:24.922 --> 40:27.299
You can lie to me all you want.
You can't lie to her.

40:27.383 --> 40:29.593
-I'm not lying to you.
-Yes, you are.

40:30.177 --> 40:33.931
You know this Dr. Kay. Where is Dr. Kay?

40:35.224 --> 40:36.183
I don't know--

40:42.523 --> 40:45.443
Is it really necessary to take
these lashings from Kay in person?

40:47.027 --> 40:48.821
Just shut up and drive, Akers.

40:58.622 --> 41:02.168
There's a base in the Upside Down.

41:02.751 --> 41:04.044
Gable Ridge Road.

41:04.545 --> 41:08.716
-Gable Ridge Road Base.
-What the hell is she doing to me?

41:08.799 --> 41:11.760
I don't exactly know how it works,
but I know it's probably not a good idea

41:11.844 --> 41:13.971
to have her rooting around there
for too long.

41:14.054 --> 41:16.640
What was this meeting about
with you and the good doctor?

41:16.724 --> 41:20.936
The freak. She wants the freak.
That's her mission. That's all I know.

41:22.104 --> 41:24.732
You have one more month,
Lieutenant Colonel.

41:25.357 --> 41:28.235
Then I find someone else
to lead this operation.

41:30.529 --> 41:31.739
Thank you, ma'am.

41:31.822 --> 41:33.115
Akers, let's go.

42:00.100 --> 42:01.519
There's a door at the end.

42:02.394 --> 42:04.396
Big, metal,

42:04.939 --> 42:06.398
like a vault.

42:06.482 --> 42:11.278
There's a door, a big door, secure door,
down a corridor, down a hallway.

42:11.362 --> 42:12.988
-What's behind that door?
-I don't know.

42:13.072 --> 42:14.865
What's behind that door?

42:14.949 --> 42:17.743
I told you I don't know. God!

42:22.790 --> 42:26.085
There's something back there.
He doesn't want me to see.

42:27.461 --> 42:30.381
-My head! My head!
-Hey, I can make it stop.

42:30.464 --> 42:32.675
What's behind the door?

42:32.758 --> 42:35.511
Secret shit. I don't know.
Just get the freak out, man.

42:40.182 --> 42:42.560
I can make it stop,
but you gotta tell me the truth.

42:42.643 --> 42:43.727
What's behind that door?

42:43.811 --> 42:45.479
Does it have something to do
with the wall?

42:45.563 --> 42:46.855
I told you I don't know.

42:46.939 --> 42:49.233
Come on! What's behind the door?!

43:00.828 --> 43:04.623
I swear to God, I don't know!

43:04.707 --> 43:07.334
Just get her out of my head!
Get her out of my head!

43:12.047 --> 43:13.132
Hey, hey, hey!

43:18.304 --> 43:19.138
Hey!

43:24.226 --> 43:26.103
Hey! Hey!

43:27.146 --> 43:29.648
What the hell was that? What happened?

43:29.732 --> 43:32.443
El, are you all right? El?

43:32.526 --> 43:33.444
Kryptonite.

43:33.527 --> 43:34.695
What?

43:34.778 --> 43:37.865
I heard it behind the door,
louder than before.

43:38.449 --> 43:40.117
The doctor's keeping someone there,

43:40.743 --> 43:42.453
someone powerful like me.

43:43.787 --> 43:44.955
It has to be.

43:45.539 --> 43:46.790
It has to be what?

43:47.750 --> 43:48.876
The military,

43:49.877 --> 43:50.961
they have him.

43:53.172 --> 43:54.423
They have Vecna.

43:57.092 --> 44:01.972
It doesn't make sense. Henry said never
to go into the woods. Never, ever.

44:04.725 --> 44:06.685
Why am I talking to you anyways?

44:07.895 --> 44:10.856
You're a pop star.
What do you know about monsters?

44:30.292 --> 44:31.835
What would you do?

45:08.956 --> 45:10.124
Stupid.

45:40.654 --> 45:42.781
It smells like ass in here, dipshit.

45:42.865 --> 45:45.075
Probably from all my farts.

45:45.159 --> 45:46.618
Disgusting.

45:46.702 --> 45:48.120
Mom wants you down for dinner.

45:48.203 --> 45:50.372
Mom can suck a fat one.

45:55.127 --> 45:56.295
Hey!

45:58.046 --> 46:00.090
Tina! Give it back, Tina!

46:01.425 --> 46:02.885
Tina!

46:05.637 --> 46:07.598
Ah, ah, ah. Enough.

46:08.182 --> 46:12.436
How many times must I repeat myself?
This home is not a playground.

46:14.021 --> 46:18.817
Derek, wash up.
Tina, get the door, and be polite.

46:18.901 --> 46:20.444
Unless it's a Mormon.

46:20.527 --> 46:21.695
Or a Democrat.

46:22.654 --> 46:25.783
Listen, I know
you probably hate me right now,

46:26.492 --> 46:29.369
but I thought
you might want your favorite pie.

46:30.037 --> 46:33.207
And also, I just wanted to say
that I'm sorry.

46:33.290 --> 46:36.835
I'm so sorry, Tina.

46:44.927 --> 46:45.928
She's in.

46:46.762 --> 46:47.679
She's in.

46:48.847 --> 46:49.681
Hey. What…

46:49.765 --> 46:51.809
Sinclair, come in. Do you copy?

46:52.976 --> 46:55.437
Yep, this is Sinclair. Copy. Go ahead.

46:55.521 --> 46:59.066
Sinclair, I'm confused. I thought
your sister said that Tina was mean.

46:59.149 --> 47:01.735
Oh, no, no.
She's not mean. She's a villain.

47:01.819 --> 47:03.946
Kill the puppies
for a fur coat kind of villain.

47:04.029 --> 47:05.197
Trust me.

47:06.323 --> 47:08.116
How long before the drugs kick in?

47:08.200 --> 47:10.828
-Depends how much pie they eat.
-And how fast they eat it.

47:10.911 --> 47:14.289
-What they had for lunch.
-Caffeine intake, alcohol intake.

47:14.373 --> 47:15.541
It's a lot of variables.

47:15.624 --> 47:17.376
Yeah, what could go wrong, right?

47:18.460 --> 47:20.170
Aside from everything.

47:23.549 --> 47:26.635
Aw, you know,
I'm so happy you girls made up.

47:26.718 --> 47:28.679
We've missed you, Erica. Haven't we, dear?

47:28.762 --> 47:31.348
-We missed this pie, that's for sure.
-Hmm.

47:31.431 --> 47:34.017
Now, Erica,
you've done something different this time.

47:34.101 --> 47:35.102
Sorry?

47:35.185 --> 47:38.981
Your pie. It's got
a little… something extra tonight.

47:39.064 --> 47:40.732
A little hint of…

47:40.816 --> 47:41.650
Nutmeg.

47:41.733 --> 47:43.652
Nutmeg! Of course.

47:43.735 --> 47:47.197
Brilliant. Brilliant. Brill… Brilliant.

47:47.281 --> 47:49.700
Tina, aren't you gonna try some?

47:49.783 --> 47:53.996
Oh, I wish. Looks super good.
Just gotta watch those calories, you know.

47:54.079 --> 47:55.747
Fatty McFatFat.

47:55.831 --> 47:57.875
Derek, remember what we talked about.

47:57.958 --> 48:01.169
If you don't have something nice to say,
don't say it at all.

48:01.253 --> 48:04.840
This is how
you alienate your spears, Derek.

48:04.923 --> 48:06.091
My spears?

48:06.174 --> 48:10.429
Your spears. Sph… Spheres. Peers.

48:10.512 --> 48:12.681
Holy shit, Dad's wasted again.

48:12.764 --> 48:14.933
Derek. Please, language.

48:15.017 --> 48:19.021
Well, I used a low-fat creamer,
so you can enjoy guilt-free.

48:19.104 --> 48:21.481
Thanks, but I'm just not hungry.

48:22.065 --> 48:23.650
But I made it for you.

48:23.734 --> 48:25.694
I said I'm not hungry.

48:25.777 --> 48:27.029
Just a bite or two.

48:27.112 --> 48:29.323
-Okay, why are you being so weird?
-What?

48:29.406 --> 48:31.617
Why do you care so much
if I eat your stupid pie?

48:31.700 --> 48:33.368
Because it's for you.

48:33.452 --> 48:35.662
Oh my God.
It's because you want me fat, isn't it?

48:35.746 --> 48:38.123
-Girls, please.
-Why would I want you fat?

48:38.206 --> 48:40.167
Because you're still jealous
of me and Josh,

48:40.250 --> 48:42.669
and you wanna sabotage our chances
of being together.

48:42.753 --> 48:45.213
I was never jealous of you and Josh.

48:45.297 --> 48:48.592
-Then how do you explain PE?
-It was an accident.

48:48.675 --> 48:50.928
Ken, where are you going?

48:51.011 --> 48:52.346
I'm not feeling good.

48:52.429 --> 48:53.889
It wasn't an accident.

48:53.972 --> 48:56.683
It was dodgeball.
In dodgeball, you throw balls at people.

48:56.767 --> 49:00.312
Not that hard. You gave Joshy
a black eye. Now he won't even look at me.

49:00.395 --> 49:02.731
That's stupid. You didn't throw the ball.

49:02.814 --> 49:04.608
It doesn't matter. He associates us.

49:04.691 --> 49:07.611
He associates us. And you humiliated him.

49:07.694 --> 49:11.073
He humiliated himself
by crying like a goddamn pussy.

49:15.243 --> 49:16.119
Ken?

49:19.414 --> 49:20.499
Oh my God.

49:21.208 --> 49:22.042
Mommy!

49:22.125 --> 49:23.126
Mommy!

49:25.253 --> 49:26.171
Mom.

49:26.254 --> 49:28.465
Erica, call 911! Erica!

49:28.548 --> 49:29.633
Mom, wake up.

49:30.258 --> 49:31.093
Erica!

49:31.176 --> 49:33.720
Mommy, wake up. Daddy.

49:33.804 --> 49:35.973
Erica, I told you to call 911.

49:36.056 --> 49:40.310
And I told you to eat your damn pie.

52:26.560 --> 52:28.270
-This is gonna work.
-It better work.

52:28.353 --> 52:30.897
It's not like we're conspicuous
or anything.

52:35.360 --> 52:38.238
Hey. Talk to me, guys.
How's it looking out there?

52:38.321 --> 52:39.281
It's boring.

52:39.364 --> 52:41.408
How are the Turnbows holding up?

52:41.491 --> 52:45.912
They're still in their "food comas,"
but I swear to God, this Demo better show.

52:45.996 --> 52:47.956
If we took out an entire family
for nothing,

52:48.039 --> 52:50.584
my conscience will never recover.

52:59.384 --> 53:00.594
I thought you quit.

53:01.178 --> 53:02.345
Quit what?

53:03.722 --> 53:04.806
Pretty smooth.

53:05.307 --> 53:06.349
Thanks.

53:06.850 --> 53:08.226
Where's your coat?

53:08.310 --> 53:09.603
It's in the barn.

53:09.686 --> 53:12.772
Well, you should get it
if you're gonna be out here.

53:14.399 --> 53:15.400
Mom,

53:16.151 --> 53:17.235
about this morning…

53:17.319 --> 53:18.653
Will, it's fine.

53:18.737 --> 53:20.322
No, no, it's not.

53:20.405 --> 53:24.993
I shouldn't have talked to you that way,
and I was a jerk, and I'm sorry.

53:25.076 --> 53:27.162
Honey, I'm sorry too.

53:28.288 --> 53:29.789
I know I can be…

53:30.624 --> 53:32.292
I can be a lot.

53:33.335 --> 53:34.753
That's not true.

53:35.587 --> 53:38.924
It's just,
when I couldn't find you this morning…

53:39.674 --> 53:40.508
I don't know.

53:42.677 --> 53:45.847
I think about that night all the time.

53:46.640 --> 53:48.225
The night it came for you,

53:48.308 --> 53:50.310
the night all this started.

53:50.393 --> 53:53.063
I wasn't even home.

53:53.772 --> 53:55.190
My shift ran late.

53:55.273 --> 53:57.234
When I finally do get home, what do I do?

53:57.317 --> 54:04.157
I smoke cigarettes, drink cheap wine,
and watch Cheers reruns until I pass out.

54:05.408 --> 54:08.954
I didn't know you were missing
for eight hours.

54:09.037 --> 54:12.707
Mom, what happened to me,
it's not your fault.

54:12.791 --> 54:14.626
Eight hours.

54:16.836 --> 54:20.131
What kind of mother
doesn't check on their 11-year-old boy?

54:23.051 --> 54:24.511
That is ridiculous!

54:24.594 --> 54:27.097
The jury's still out on your new friend.

54:28.306 --> 54:30.934
She certainly is interesting.

54:32.769 --> 54:35.939
But one thing I know for sure,

54:36.523 --> 54:38.024
she's not your mom.

54:38.608 --> 54:41.319
She hasn't seen what I've seen,

54:41.403 --> 54:43.613
and I am not gonna look away.

54:43.697 --> 54:48.743
Not again.
Not until this is over, and you're safe.

54:48.827 --> 54:54.708
You don't have to look away, Mom.
I… I just… I need you to trust me.

54:55.417 --> 54:57.544
I do trust you, Will.

54:57.627 --> 55:01.047
But, you know, trust is a two-way street.

55:02.632 --> 55:07.595
Even though my plan last night
kind of sucked…

55:08.263 --> 55:10.390
-Kind of?
-Hey!

55:13.143 --> 55:14.686
Let's get your coat on.

55:14.769 --> 55:17.564
It's a lot harder to save the world
if you have the sniffles.

55:21.026 --> 55:25.155
So, like, what kind of criminals
does your uncle defend exactly?

55:25.238 --> 55:27.699
You know,
are they, like, white-collar criminals?

55:27.782 --> 55:30.493
Because that does seem like
a Harrington thing to do,

55:30.577 --> 55:32.412
like, defend rich douchebags.

55:32.495 --> 55:33.496
And in this situation,

55:33.580 --> 55:36.541
I think that the rich douchebags
would be coming for us.

55:39.919 --> 55:40.754
Steve?

55:40.837 --> 55:42.589
Steve? Are you there?

55:42.672 --> 55:44.341
Yeah, I hear you. Just stop talking.

55:44.424 --> 55:45.842
I think we've got company.

55:47.344 --> 55:50.555
Moving south down Arlington,
T-minus 30 seconds.

55:50.638 --> 55:52.891
South down Arlington, T-minus 30 seconds.

55:52.974 --> 55:54.559
Status check. Taggers?

55:54.642 --> 55:56.811
In position and set. Launcher?

55:56.895 --> 55:58.772
Set. Catcher?

55:59.356 --> 56:00.690
Set. Trackers?

56:01.691 --> 56:03.818
Set. Let's do this thing already.

56:18.291 --> 56:19.292
It's inside.

56:19.376 --> 56:20.502
Minimize chatter.

56:20.585 --> 56:22.545
It's inside. Keep your traps shut.

57:25.442 --> 57:26.401
Catch this!

58:01.269 --> 58:02.312
Get him!

58:11.654 --> 58:13.114
Now!

58:19.078 --> 58:20.079
Nancy!

58:20.663 --> 58:23.082
Nancy! Hurry! Come on!

58:26.669 --> 58:29.297
Get him, Mike! Get him, Mike!
Mike, get him! Get him!

58:31.841 --> 58:32.800
Ah!

58:35.970 --> 58:37.639
It flipped! It flipped!

58:37.722 --> 58:41.684
Signal acquired. Headed our way.

58:41.768 --> 58:42.852
How close?

58:44.062 --> 58:45.230
Dustin, how close?

58:46.773 --> 58:48.858
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

58:48.942 --> 58:51.069
Shit.

58:51.152 --> 58:52.612
Jesus Christ!

58:53.404 --> 58:54.364
Where is it?

58:54.447 --> 58:56.032
Hold your horses.

58:58.243 --> 59:00.370
Bearing northwest and fast.

59:01.204 --> 59:03.581
-Oh, come on.
-Demo tagged and released.

59:03.665 --> 59:07.210
Trackers in pursuit.
Repeat, trackers in pursuit. Hit it!

59:12.590 --> 59:15.552
All right, signal holding.
Just keep steady.

59:16.553 --> 59:18.096
Holding. Turn right.

59:18.680 --> 59:20.515
-Right?
-Right! Turn right! Right now!

59:28.439 --> 59:29.816
Sorry, sorry, sorry!

59:31.568 --> 59:33.027
Whoa! You're gonna crash!

59:33.111 --> 59:34.821
-You said right!
-Jesus Christ!

59:36.739 --> 59:39.325
Stop! Stop! Stop right now! Stop here!

59:41.327 --> 59:43.788
God damn it! Henderson, what are we doing?

59:43.871 --> 59:44.998
We lost the signal!

59:45.081 --> 59:47.333
-Come on. Come on!
-Shit, shit, shit.

59:47.417 --> 59:48.626
Shit, shit, shit.

59:48.710 --> 59:51.629
-I got it! It's headed southeast now!
-God damn it.

59:52.422 --> 59:53.464
-Jesus!
-Sorry!

59:54.215 --> 59:55.216
It's okay.

59:55.300 --> 59:57.302
-Whoa, whoa, whoa! Shit!
-Hang on!

59:58.595 --> 59:59.596
Shit, shit, shit!

59:59.679 --> 1:00:01.347
Jesus Christ.

1:00:01.431 --> 1:00:02.515
All right, I've got it.

1:00:02.599 --> 1:00:04.517
-You got it?
-Yes, I got it.

1:00:13.901 --> 1:00:15.320
Why would they turn around?

1:00:15.403 --> 1:00:17.155
Maybe he's trying to shake them?

1:00:17.238 --> 1:00:20.033
No, that's impossible.
It doesn't know it's being tracked.

1:00:25.288 --> 1:00:27.415
Stay away from me! Stay away!

1:00:27.498 --> 1:00:28.916
No, no, no, no, no.

1:00:29.000 --> 1:00:31.044
I'm so, so sorry, okay?

1:00:31.127 --> 1:00:34.255
I'll probably explain this at some point,
but for now, don't move.

1:00:34.339 --> 1:00:36.466
-I thought he ate, like, two slices.
-He did!

1:00:36.549 --> 1:00:37.675
Why is he awake then?

1:00:37.759 --> 1:00:38.885
It doesn't matter.

1:00:39.802 --> 1:00:40.845
Not anymore.

1:00:52.106 --> 1:00:53.441
We're southeast.

1:00:53.983 --> 1:00:55.693
That's why it turned around.

1:00:59.405 --> 1:01:00.740
Vecna's seen.

1:01:01.574 --> 1:01:02.784
He knows where we are.

1:02:20.695 --> 1:02:22.238
Hello?

1:02:22.947 --> 1:02:24.198
Henry?

1:02:25.283 --> 1:02:26.492
Are you there?

1:02:31.497 --> 1:02:32.915
Henry?

1:03:30.807 --> 1:03:31.724
Hi.

1:03:55.206 --> 1:03:57.792
Children behave

1:03:58.793 --> 1:04:02.380
That's what they say
When we're together

1:04:02.463 --> 1:04:06.008
And watch how you play

1:04:06.092 --> 1:04:08.511
They don't understand and so we're

1:04:08.594 --> 1:04:11.722
Running just as fast as we can

1:04:12.807 --> 1:04:15.935
Holdin' onto one another's hand

1:04:16.602 --> 1:04:19.522
Tryin' to get away into the night

1:04:19.605 --> 1:04:21.440
And then you put your arms around me

1:04:21.524 --> 1:04:23.860
And we tumble to the ground
And then you say

1:04:23.943 --> 1:04:27.321
I think we're alone now

1:04:27.405 --> 1:04:31.033
There doesn't seem to be anyone around

1:04:31.951 --> 1:04:34.537
I think we're alone now

1:04:34.620 --> 1:04:38.708
The beating of our hearts
Is the only sound

1:04:46.674 --> 1:04:49.218
Look at the way

1:04:50.636 --> 1:04:53.222
We gotta hide what we're doin'

1:04:53.306 --> 1:04:57.184
'Cause what would they say

1:04:57.268 --> 1:04:59.896
If they ever knew and so we're

1:04:59.979 --> 1:05:03.900
Running just as fast as we can

1:05:03.983 --> 1:05:07.403
Holdin' onto one another's hand

1:05:07.486 --> 1:05:10.573
